<br>
Some spells might be innately evil (protection from good or words that just cause straight death i.e. finger'o'death), but others might have some more positive uses even though they are classified as evil such as animate dead.<br>
<br>
Will there be ways for some of the more shady PC casters can utilize some 'evil' spells without their alignment slipping, or will they simply be off limits from PC to avoid any unnecessary loss of alignment?  This may sound like a weird question, but doing certain acts will cause a change in alignment, and in some extreme cases loss of abilities (paladin that does something un-lawful good can slip and lose his status as a paladin automatically I had read somewhere).<br>
<br>
Just curious how this will be handled as i often enjoyed 'creative spell use' when playing the old pen and paper games. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/usegalsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Segal SoulSaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Assistant GM</span><br>  Posts: 2303<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(6/23/01 4:39:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Current list of in-game spells</span><hr size=1> Well Alignment is dynamic and handled by the AI so I cant answer your question completely.  I assume that neutral cleric will be able to cause wounds, I would not consider this an evil act unless you started using it on local merchants.  Things like pickpocketing automatically give negative alignment hits so you could work yourself to the dark side that way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/uamberyllarydunmorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amberyll Arydunmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 995<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(6/23/01 4:54:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Current list of in-game spells</span><hr size=1> So that innocent wizard who casts animate dead in order to help out with the household chores might also be considered slipping to the dark side =)  I think some spells will need to be played with in the testing stages to see if the mere casting of them will cause someone to become evil, or if only the evil uses of them cause the alignment slip.  Even with pick pockets, i can see times when, if used properly and on specific individuals, i could see where it should not cause an alignment slip, but am unsure whether the AI would ever be able to differentiate between good picking vs. bad picking or likewise between innocent evil spell usage vs. evil evil spell usage =) <p>Amberyll Arydunmorn<br>
